{
  "topicId": "m10-t1",
  "title": "Asking for Travel & Transportation Services in Darija",
  "dialect": "darija",
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Basic Greetings",
          "arabic": "تحيات أساسية"
        },
        "text": "Starting a conversation politely is key in Moroccan Darija. Learn these common greetings to initiate your requests.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "السلام عليكم",
            "english": "Hello / Peace be upon you",
            "transliteration": "As-salamu alaykum"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "كي داير؟",
            "english": "How are you? (to male)",
            "transliteration": "Ki dayr?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "كي دايرة؟",
            "english": "How are you? (to female)",
            "transliteration": "Ki dayra?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Expressing \"I want\"",
          "arabic": "التعبير عن 'أريد'"
        },
        "text": "The phrase 'بغيت' (bghit) is essential for stating your needs or intentions, such as wanting a service or to go somewhere.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "بغيت",
            "english": "I want",
            "transliteration": "Bghit"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "بغيت نمشي لـ...",
            "english": "I want to go to...",
            "transliteration": "Bghit nmshi l..."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking \"Do you have?\"",
          "arabic": "السؤال 'هل لديك؟'"
        },
        "text": "To inquire about the availability of a service or an item, use 'واش عندك؟'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "واش عندك؟",
            "english": "Do you have? (singular)",
            "transliteration": "Wach 3andk?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "واش عندكم؟",
            "english": "Do you have? (plural/formal)",
            "transliteration": "Wach 3andkom?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "السلام عليكم، بغيت نمشي لـ...",
        "english": "Hello, I want to go to...",
        "transliteration": "As-salamu alaykum, bghit nmshi l..."
      },
      "context": "A polite way to start a request for a destination."
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "كي داير؟ واش عندك شي طاكسي؟",
        "english": "How are you? Do you have a taxi?",
        "transliteration": "Ki dayr? Wach 3andk shi taxi?"
      },
      "context": "Asking a taxi driver or a local if a taxi is available."
    },
